society, those concerned with the provision of health care are especially 
affected. With chronic disease replacing acute illness, and costs of care 
mounting, health-care providers will require a comprehensive assessment of its 
older citizens so as to be able to provide cost-effective care across all sites, 
be that location a hospital or, more frequently, the home. The development of 
such capabilities is already under way by the InterRA1 group, an international 
group of investigators.

